<paragraph id="8B81794EFFD9E671FF7DBC5A7B5EBE4A" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
Mesosoma (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FEF5BC5A7FC6BC6E" box="[335,428,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A‒C, P. ardens: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, oblique-dorsal view; C, clypeus. D-F, P. awbalus: D, habitus, lateral view; E, head, oblique-dorsal view; F, clypeus. [A‒C: Holotype, ROME159196; D-F: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223045/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Figs 2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FE0DBC5A7C61BC6E" box="[439,523,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A, B, P. ardens: A, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; B, prepectus. C, D, P. awbalus: C, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; D, prepectus. [A and B: Holotype, ROME159196; C and D: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223047/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">3A, 3B</figureCitation>
): length about 1.1× maximum width. Pronotum in dorsal view: short, about 0.25× length of mesoscutum, PN/MSC 0.2‒0.3; slightly shorter along midline, 0.7‒0.8× length laterad; anterior margin rounded; with flange on pronotal panel at the level of mesothoracic spiracle. Lateral panel of pronotum (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FA8FBC127BE5BC16" box="[1333,1423,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A, B, P. ardens: A, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; B, prepectus. C, D, P. awbalus: C, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; D, prepectus. [A and B: Holotype, ROME159196; C and D: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223047/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
): narrower than prepectus, LPP/PPT approximately 0.6; flat, with 2 rows of punctures with narrow interspaces, vantrad with narrow coriarious patch; anterior margin rounded; posterior margin ventrad nearly flat, with row of alveolae. Prepectus: broad; differentiated from pronotum, with distinct suture; ventral strap short (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FB3DBCEE7AB5BCA2" box="[1159,1247,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A, B, P. ardens: A, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; B, prepectus. C, D, P. awbalus: C, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; D, prepectus. [A and B: Holotype, ROME159196; C and D: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223047/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
, arrow), without row of alveolae; central area smooth, with foveae along dorsal and posterior margins. Femoral depression: weakly rugose, with foveae. Midlobe of mesoscutum (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FD18BCA67C94BF6A" box="[674,766,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A, B, P. ardens: A, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; B, prepectus. C, D, P. awbalus: C, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; D, prepectus. [A and B: Holotype, ROME159196; C and D: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223047/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
): with raised scale-like tubercle (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FBCBBCA67AA3BF6A" box="[1137,1225,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A, B, P. ardens: A, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; B, prepectus. C, D, P. awbalus: C, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; D, prepectus. [A and B: Holotype, ROME159196; C and D: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223047/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
, arrow); punctures angulate, with narrow interspaces. Lateral lobe of mesoscutum: weakly rugulose dorsad; rugulose-punctate laterad. Scutellum (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FEACBF1E7F1ABF12" box="[278,368,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A, B, P. ardens: A, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; B, prepectus. C, D, P. awbalus: C, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; D, prepectus. [A and B: Holotype, ROME159196; C and D: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223047/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
): about as long as mesoscutum, SC/MSC approximately 1.1; posterior margin smoothly rounded; with angulate punctures and narrow interspaces. Axilla: punctate dorsad, imbricate below. Axillula: wide triangular lobe, as long as width at base, smooth. Propodeum: length along midline about 0.3× width of propodeum; submedian area shagreened to smooth, with weak groove along median carina; alveolate-rugose laterad; without distinct lateral plicae, delimited ventrad by plicae, dorsad by transverse band of foveae; propodeal spiracle margin reticulate ventrad; nucha rugulose. Fore wing (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FD85BFA27CF7BE66" box="[575,669,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A‒C, P. ardens: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, oblique-dorsal view; C, clypeus. D-F, P. awbalus: D, habitus, lateral view; E, head, oblique-dorsal view; F, clypeus. [A‒C: Holotype, ROME159196; D-F: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223045/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
): hyaline, with yellow venations; postmarginal vein long, 0.8‒0.9× length of marginal vein, approximately twice length of stigmal vein; stigmal vein rounded without uncus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B81794EFFD9E671FF7DBE1A7FE7BEF2" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
Metasoma (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FEF7BE1A7FC0BE2E" box="[333,426,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A, B, P. ardens: A, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; B, prepectus. C, D, P. awbalus: C, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; D, prepectus. [A and B: Holotype, ROME159196; C and D: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223047/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
): petiole short and straplike, smooth, without raised scale; Gt2 smooth, posterior margin concave; Gt3 smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B81794EFFD9E671FF7DBED27FECBED6" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1185]" box="[199,390,907,933]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Male: Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3242AC5FFD9E671FF7DBEF77FF8B9D2" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B81794EFFD9E671FF7DBEF77FF8B9D2" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis id="B94AA55CFFD9E671FF7DBEF77F50BEBB" bold="true" box="[199,314,942,968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E02CDFFD9E671FEF2BEF67C70BEBA" box="[328,538,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Perilampidae" genus="Perilampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ardens">
<emphasis id="B94AA55CFFD9E671FEF2BEF67C70BEBA" box="[328,538,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Perilampus ardens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E02CDFFD9E671FCFFBEF67DD4BEBA" authorityName="Yoo and Darling" authorityYear="2021" box="[837,958,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Perilampidae" genus="Perilampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="awbalus">
<emphasis id="B94AA55CFFD9E671FCFFBEF67DD4BEBA" box="[837,958,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">P. awbalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E02CDFFD9E671FC48BEF67A33BEBB" box="[1010,1113,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Perilampidae" genus="Perilampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seyrigi">
<emphasis id="B94AA55CFFD9E671FC48BEF67A33BEBB" box="[1010,1113,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">P. seyrigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the following: transverse clypeus (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FF46BE8A7F3EBE9E" box="[252,340,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A‒C, P. ardens: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, oblique-dorsal view; C, clypeus. D-F, P. awbalus: D, habitus, lateral view; E, head, oblique-dorsal view; F, clypeus. [A‒C: Holotype, ROME159196; D-F: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223045/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
), green-blue body coloration (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FD1FBE8A7D68BE9E" box="[677,770,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A‒C, P. ardens: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, oblique-dorsal view; C, clypeus. D-F, P. awbalus: D, habitus, lateral view; E, head, oblique-dorsal view; F, clypeus. [A‒C: Holotype, ROME159196; D-F: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223045/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Figs 2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FCB4BE8A7D59BE9E" box="[782,819,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A, B, P. ardens: A, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; B, prepectus. C, D, P. awbalus: C, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; D, prepectus. [A and B: Holotype, ROME159196; C and D: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223047/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">3A</figureCitation>
), vertex rounded behind (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FBE8BE8A7AC0BE9E" box="[1106,1194,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A‒C, P. ardens: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, oblique-dorsal view; C, clypeus. D-F, P. awbalus: D, habitus, lateral view; E, head, oblique-dorsal view; F, clypeus. [A‒C: Holotype, ROME159196; D-F: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223045/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
), occiput with furrow extended along midline of vertex (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FDA4BEAE7C1CB962" box="[542,630,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A‒C, P. ardens: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, oblique-dorsal view; C, clypeus. D-F, P. awbalus: D, habitus, lateral view; E, head, oblique-dorsal view; F, clypeus. [A‒C: Holotype, ROME159196; D-F: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223045/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
, arrow), higher scale-like tubercle on the midlobe of mesoscutum (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FAD5BEAE7ED1B946" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A, B, P. ardens: A, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; B, prepectus. C, D, P. awbalus: C, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; D, prepectus. [A and B: Holotype, ROME159196; C and D: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223047/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
, arrow), narrower pronotum (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FDBCB9427C37B946" box="[518,605,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A, B, P. ardens: A, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; B, prepectus. C, D, P. awbalus: C, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; D, prepectus. [A and B: Holotype, ROME159196; C and D: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223047/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
), and smooth Gt3 (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FC8BB9427DE0B946" box="[817,906,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A, B, P. ardens: A, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; B, prepectus. C, D, P. awbalus: C, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; D, prepectus. [A and B: Holotype, ROME159196; C and D: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223047/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E02CDFFD9E671FC27B9427A1AB946" box="[925,1136,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Perilampidae" genus="Perilampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ardens">
<emphasis id="B94AA55CFFD9E671FC27B9427A1AB946" box="[925,1136,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Perilampus ardens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E02CDFFD9E671FF0EB9667F4CB92B" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1798" box="[180,294,1087,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Perilampidae" genus="Perilampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auratus">
<emphasis id="B94AA55CFFD9E671FF0EB9667F4CB92B" box="[180,294,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">P. auratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the convex clypeal margin (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FC1AB9667D92B92A" box="[928,1016,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A‒C, P. ardens: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, oblique-dorsal view; C, clypeus. D-F, P. awbalus: D, habitus, lateral view; E, head, oblique-dorsal view; F, clypeus. [A‒C: Holotype, ROME159196; D-F: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223045/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
), red and yellow iridescent margin of the scale on the mesoscutum (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FE50B93A7C29B90E" box="[490,579,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A, B, P. ardens: A, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; B, prepectus. C, D, P. awbalus: C, mesosoma and head, dorsal view; D, prepectus. [A and B: Holotype, ROME159196; C and D: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223047/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) and the wrinkled edge of scrobal cavity (
<figureCitation id="130565CBFFD9E671FB98B93A7A11B90E" box="[1058,1147,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[164,1423,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Perilampus ardens and P. awbalus. A‒C, P. ardens: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, oblique-dorsal view; C, clypeus. D-F, P. awbalus: D, habitus, lateral view; E, head, oblique-dorsal view; F, clypeus. [A‒C: Holotype, ROME159196; D-F: Holotype, ROME174255]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223045/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). See also Appendix 1, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E02CDFFD9E671FA32B93A7E87B9D3" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1798" class="Insecta" family="Perilampidae" genus="Perilampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auratus">
<emphasis id="B94AA55CFFD9E671FA32B93A7E87B9D3" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">P. auratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E02CDFFD9E671FE99B9DE7FE1B9D3" box="[291,395,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Perilampidae" genus="Perilampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seyrigi">
<emphasis id="B94AA55CFFD9E671FE99B9DE7FE1B9D3" box="[291,395,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">P. seyrigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
